    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-06T01:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-06T01:54:00-05:00" n="836"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7490F/11–644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-06T10:00:00+03:06"
                            >November 6, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 6—9:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>332. ReDept’s 234, November 3, 7 p.m. Request to Saudi Government delivered
                    yesterday. However it is possible Saudi Government will await British
                    concurrence before replying just as they require prior concurrence in Dhahran
                    airdrome (Legation’s 330 November 3, 3 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] pm.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d836fn2">Not printed.</note>). I hope Department can follow request
                    with British concurrence in Saudi radio telegraph station earliest possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
